      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a peerless example of the S54-powered legend. Featuring the high-revving 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing, the mechanical synchronization is flawless. The 6-speed Getrag manual transmission offers crisp, short-throw engagements, sending power to the rear wheels via a factory M-Variable differential lock. The chassis has undergone preventive subframe reinforcement and retains its factory-fresh torsional rigidity. Finished in Carbon Black over Nappa leather, the exterior exhibits zero clear-coat degradation or rock chips. This is a collector-grade specimen with a fully documented service pedigree and an immaculate undercarriage.",
